= Wikitext Syntax =
=== Basic Syntax ===
Add the `layerset` parameter to any file link to display annotations:

<code><nowiki>[[File: Example.jpg | layerset=on]]</nowiki></code><br>
'''Note:''' 'layers=' is also supported for backwards compatibility. Both parameters work identically.

=== 'layerset=' Parameter Values ===
{| class='wikitable'
! Value !! Effect 
|-
| <code>on</code> || Display the default layer set
|-
| <code>default</code> || Display the default layer set (explicit)
|-
| <code>SetName</code> || Display a specific named layer set
|-
| <code>off</code> || Explicitly disable layers
|-
| <code>none</code> || Explicitly disable layers (alternative)
|}

=== Examples ===
'''Default layer set:'''<br>
<code><nowiki>[[File: Diagram.png | layerset=on]]</nowiki></code><br>
<code><nowiki>[[File: Diagram.png | layerset=default]]</nowiki></code><br>
Both of these display the default layer set on '''Diagram.png'''.

'''Named layer sets:'''<br>
<code><nowiki>[[File: Heart.png | layerset=anatomy]]</nowiki></code><br>
<code><nowiki>[[File: Heart.png | layerset=blood-flow]]</nowiki></code></br>
Both of these display '''Heart.png''' but with different layer sets.

'''No layer sets:'''<br>
<code><nowiki>[[File: Diagram.png | layerset=off]]</nowiki></code></br>
<code><nowiki>[[File: Diagram.png | layerset=none]]</nowiki></code></br>
<code><nowiki>[[File: Diagram.png]]</nowiki></code></br>
These examples display '''Diagram.png''' with no layer set.

=== Combining with Image Parameters ===
The 'layerset' parameter works with all standard MediaWiki image parameters:<br>
'''Thumbnails'''<br>
<code><nowiki>[[File: Diagram.png | thumb | layerset=on | Diagram with annotations]]</nowiki></code></br>
<code><nowiki>[[File: Diagram.png | thumb | 300px | layerset=anatomy | Anatomical labels]]</nowiki></code>

'''Alignment'''<br>
<code><nowiki>[[File: Diagram.png | left | layerset=on]]</nowiki></code></br>
<code><nowiki>[[File: Diagram.png | center | layerset=on]]</nowiki></code></br>
<code><nowiki>[[File: Diagram.png | right | layerset=on]]</nowiki></code>

'''Size'''<br>
<code><nowiki>[[File: Diagram.png | 200px | layerset=on]]</nowiki></code></br>
<code><nowiki>[[File: Diagram.png | 300x200px | layerset=on]]</nowiki></code>

'''Border and Framing'''<br>
<code><nowiki>[[File: Diagram.png | border | layerset=on]]</nowiki></code></br>
<code><nowiki>[[File: Diagram.png | frame | layerset=on | Caption text]]</nowiki></code></br>
<code><nowiki>[[File: Diagram.png | frameless | layerset=on]]</nowiki></code>

'''Complete Example'''<br>
<code><nowiki>[[File: Human_Heart.png | thumb | 400px | right | border | layerset=anatomy | Human heart with anatomical labels]]</nowiki></code>

=== Link Behavior (layerslink=) ===
Control what happens when users click on layered images with the 'layerslink=' parameter:<br>
'''Note:''' 'layerslink=' must be used together with 'layerset='. It controls the click behavior for images that have layers enabled. Without 'layerset=' or 'layers=', the 'layerslink=' parameter has no effect.
{| class='wikitable'
! Value !! Effect
|-
| (none) || Standard MediaWiki link to File page
|-
| 'editor' || Opens the layer editor, returns to originating page on close
|-
| 'editor-newtab' || Opens editor in a new browser tab
|-
| 'editor-modal' || Opens editor in overlay without navigation
|-
| 'viewer' || Opens fullscreen lightbox viewer
|-
| 'lightbox' || Alias for 'viewer'
|}

'''Examples'''<br>
<code><nowiki>[[File: Diagram.png | layerset=anatomy | layerslink=editor]]</nowiki></code> Opens editor</br>
<code><nowiki>[[File: Diagram.png | layerset=anatomy | layerslink=viewer]]</nowiki></code> Opens full size preview</br>
<code><nowiki>[[File: Diagram.png | layerset=anatomy | layerslink=lightbox]]</nowiki></code> Same as 'viewer'</br>
<code><nowiki>[[File: Diagram.png | layerset=anatomy]]</nowiki></code>Opens image's 'File:' page

'''Advanced Editor Modes'''<br>
For additional control over editor behavior:<br>
<code><nowiki>[[File: Diagram.png | layerset=anatomy | layerslink=editor-newtab]]</nowiki></code> Opens the editor in a new tab<br>
<code><nowiki>[[File: Diagram.png | layerset=anatomy | layerslink=editor-modal]]</nowiki></code> Opens the editor in an overlay (iframe).

'''Note:''' 'layerslink=' is a deprecated feature with the new overlay buttons [[File:Layers-overlay-buttons.png]] (edit / view full size) that display on hover.<br>
The 'Edit layers' button will open the Layers editor modally (overlay) so the user never leaves the page they are viewing. Saved edits are updated immediately on editor close.<br>
The 'View full size' button opens a 'lightbox' (overlay) preview of the image. On overlay close, no navigation takes place, so the user remains on the same page.

'''Link to editor'''<br>
Direct linking to the editor is also possible:<br>
<code>/wiki/File: Example.jpg?action=editlayers&setname=anatomy</code><br>
Supported URL parameters:<br>
- 'setname' - Layer set name to load<br>
- 'layerset' - Alias for 'setname'</br>
- 'layers' - Alias for 'setname' (backwards compatibility)

=== Behavior Notes ===
'''Non-existent Sets'''<br>
If a named set doesn't exist, no layers are displayed (silent failure). The image shows without annotations.<br>
<code><nowiki>[[File: Diagram.png | layerset=nonexistent]]</nowiki></code> If 'nonexistent' set doesn't exist, shows image only.<br>
Overlay link to editor will appear when a layer set is included. Clicking 'Edit layers' will open the editor and create the new layer set.<br>
Other 'layerslink=' parameters will also work once 'layerset=' is included.

'''Case Sensitivity'''<br>
Set names are case-sensitive.<br>
<code><nowiki>[[File: Diagram.png | layerset=Anatomy]]</nowiki></code> is not the same as <code><nowiki>[[File: Diagram.png | layerset=anatomy]]</nowiki></code><br>

'''Parameter Order'''<br>
The 'layerset' parameter can appear anywhere in the parameter list:<br>
<code><nowiki>[[File: Diagram.png | layerset=on | thumb | 300px]]</nowiki></code><br>
<code><nowiki>[[File: Diagram.png | thumb | layerset=on | 300px]]</nowiki></code><br>
<code><nowiki>[[File: Diagram.png | thumb | 300px | layerset=on]]</nowiki></code><br>
All three examples behave exactly the same.

= Slide Mode =
Create standalone graphics without a base image using the <code><nowiki>{{#slide:}}</nowiki></code> parser function:<br>
<code><nowiki>{{#slide: MySlideName}}</nowiki></code><br>
<code><nowiki>{{#Slide: ... }}</nowiki></code> Capitalized 'Slide' is also supported for backwards compatibility.

Just like images, slides support multiple named layer sets.

'''Slide Parameters'''
{| class="wikitable"
! Parameter !! Description !! Example !! More
|-
| layerset || Named layer set to display || layerset=english || Same as with images
|-
|canvas || Canvas size (WxH) || canvas=1920x1080 || Only used when creating a new slide, otherwise ignored<br>Canvas dimensions can be changed in the editor
|-
| size || Display size || size=800x600 || Similar to images (px omitted). Aspect ratio is preserved without exceeding stated width and height
|-
| noedit || disables edit button || noedit || this prevents the 'Edit layers' overlay button
|}

'''Basic slide''' (default layer set)<br>
<code><nowiki>{{#slide: MyDiagram}}</nowiki></code>

'''Specific named layer set'''<br>
<code><nowiki>{{#slide: MyDiagram | layerset=english}}</nowiki></code><br>
<code><nowiki>{{#slide: MyDiagram | layerset=spanish}}</nowiki></code>

'''Custom canvas and display size'''<br>
<code><nowiki>{{#slide: Infographic | canvas=1200x800 | size=600x400}}</nowiki></code>

'''View-only mode'''<br>
<code><nowiki>{{#slide: Published | noedit}}</nowiki></code>
